note: After being crushed by Carolina last week, things don't get any easier for Zach Wilson and Gang Green as the team faces a sound New England defense and a coach known for having his way with rookie QBs. Lock in NE DST as a top-5 option in Week 2.

The Bucs' defense was scorched by Dak Prescott and Co. in Week 1, but the performance is understandable given the elite Cowboys offense. Tampa Bay is in a great bounce-back spot in Week 2 at home against a Falcons team that was crushed by Philly a week ago and put up just six points.
Houston fared well against the lowly Jags in Week 1, but they'll have a much tougher time moving the ball against the Browns' elite defense. Cleveland DST is an easy top-10 play.

Philly's offense looked strong a week ago, and while the matchup with the Falcons figures to be easier than this week's against the Niners, San Fran's defense is one to fade in Week 2. Outside of Week 1's pick-6 against the Lions, the Niners' defense didn't look elite, and with Jason Verrett on IR, I'm skeptical of a top-12 finish for this unit in the City of Brotherly Love.
The Panthers D unsurprisingly had a huge Week 1 against the lowly Jets, but a Week 2 matchup with the Saints isn't one to target. You can avoid CAR DST in this one and look for better options.
